data.title: Roll Call of Heroes: National Police Week
meta_keywords: Grand Lodge of the Fraternal Order of Police
National Law Enforcement Officers Memorial Fund
data.meta_description: National Police Week draws in between 25,000 to 40,000 attendees. The attendees come from departments throughout the United States as well as from agencies throughout the world. This provides a unique opportunity to meet others who work in law enforcement. In that spirit, the Fraternal Order of Police DC Lodge #1 sponsors receptions each afternoon and evening during Police Week. These events are open to all law enforcement personnel and are an experience unlike any other.
